===Sub-Saharan Africa=== Prior to the [[5.9 kiloyear event]] (3900 BC) and the desiccation of the [[Green Sahara]], Sub-Saharan Africa remains in the [[Later Stone Age|Paleolithic]]. The beginning of the [[Pastoral Neolithic]] falls still into the late phase of the Green Sahara, in the 6th or 5th millennium BC.<ref>Gifford-Gonzalez, Diane. (2017) "Pastoralism in sub-Saharan Africa." In ''The Oxford Handbook of Zooarchaeology,'' pp. 396-413.</ref> As the grasslands of the Sahara began drying after 3900 BC, herders would spread into the Nile Valley and by the mid 3rd millennium BC into eastern Africa.
