{{Infobox Politician |name = Anatol Țăranu |image = Anatol Țăranu (2014-10-16).png |caption = |office = Member of the [[Moldovan Parliament]] |term_start = 1990 |term_end = 1993 |predecessor = |successor = |term_start2 = 2005 |term_end2 = 2009 |predecessor2 = |successor2 = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1951|10|19|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Chişinău]] |death_date = |death_place = |party = [[National Liberal Party (Moldova)]], [[Party Alliance Our Moldova]] |otherparty = [[Popular Front of Moldova]] |spouse = [[Ludmila Lazăr]], PhD |children = Teodor, Cristian, Gabriela |alma_mater = [[Moldova State University]], 1978 |profession = |religion = [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodoxy]] }}
'''Anatol Țăranu''' (born 19 October 1951) is a [[Moldova]]n politician.
== Biography ==
Țăranu holds a Ph.D. in history, 1986, and served as member of the [[Parliament of Moldova]] (1990–1993, 2005–2009). Țăranu has also been a chief expert for the [[Chişinău]] side during negotiations with separatist leaders in [[Transnistria]]. Between 1993-1994, Țăranu was Moldovan Ambassador to [[Moscow]], and between 1997 and 1998 he was an advisor with special missions to the [[President of the Republic of Moldova]]. At the third congress of the [[Social Democratic Party (Moldova)|Social Democratic Party]], 25–26 February 1995, Anatol Țăranu was elected as a new head of the party.<ref>[http://www.e-democracy.md/parties/psd/ Partidul Social Democrat (PSD)]</ref>
After [[Moldovan parliamentary election, 2005|2005 parliamentary election]], Anatol Țăranu was excluded from [[Party Alliance Our Moldova]]. On 16 December 2006 Țăranu became a deputy chairman of the new [[National Liberal Party (Moldova)|National Liberal Party]]; Țăranu left the party in November 2008 because he disagreed with the party's decision to stand for parliament in [[Moldovan parliamentary election, April 2009|2009]] jointly with the [[European Action Movement]].<ref>[http://www.azi.md/ro/print-story/167 Balti city organization secedes from Centrist Union...]</ref>
He currently works as Director of the Political Science and Political History Centre of the [[State University of Moldova]] and at the History Institute of the [[Academy of Sciences of Moldova]], where he worked before becoming a deputy.<ref>[http://www.imedia.md/print.php?l=en&idc=270&id=700 Tăranu Anatol] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722172137/http://www.imedia.md/print.php?l=en&idc=270&id=700 |date=July 22, 2011 }}</ref>
